{
  "texts": [
    "This means that user-item interactive events in the last six months of the user are in the short-term category, and other interactions since the user's birth are in the long-term category.",
    "The data in the train set are divided into two categories: short-term interest data and long-term interest data, and then the resource recommendation is generated as the output of the model.",
    "After training the model to reach a certain error value, the test set can be used to test the efficiency of the recommendation model.",
    "Researchers have looked at short-term interests as a fixed feature in many previous works and therefore assigned the same weight to the items.",
    "As a result, diversity in short-term interests has not been properly evaluated."
  ]
}